WEBVTT

00:06.882 --> 00:09.635
[Heather] Everyone has a reason
for playing Panic.

00:11.220 --> 00:13.681
But we all have the same fear.

00:13.764 --> 00:16.642
That we're heading nowhere
but a dead end.

00:17.935 --> 00:20.604
That's why Panic ends
on the road.

00:22.648 --> 00:26.152
That's why the final challenge
is Joust.

00:26.235 --> 00:28.237
♪ ♪

00:29.363 --> 00:33.325
Two players face off at
the Phantom Hill straightaway.

00:33.409 --> 00:35.453
One road, a single lane,

00:35.536 --> 00:38.080
and half a mile each
to get nervous.

00:39.123 --> 00:40.583
- One of them will
have to swerve.
- [engine revving]

00:40.666 --> 00:43.127
Or both of them will lose
more than the game.

00:43.210 --> 00:44.545
The challenge:

00:44.628 --> 00:47.506
to make sure you're not the one
who turns the wheel.

00:47.590 --> 00:49.592
♪ ♪

00:56.849 --> 00:58.851
[monitor beeping steadily]

01:05.232 --> 01:07.193
[footsteps approach]

01:09.195 --> 01:10.404
[Heather] Why didn't you tell me

01:10.488 --> 01:11.739
Cortez was involved
in the betting ring?

01:11.822 --> 01:14.200
I thought you had your mind
made up about me.

01:14.283 --> 01:15.618
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

01:15.701 --> 01:17.328
Plus, I wasn't 100% sure.

01:17.411 --> 01:19.330
Luke kept me
out of his business.

01:19.413 --> 01:21.332
He said it was all he could do.

01:21.415 --> 01:22.917
Cortez was blackmailing him?

01:23.959 --> 01:25.586
Yeah.
Said he was working a sting.

01:25.669 --> 01:27.171
So he could help him
get out of trouble

01:27.254 --> 01:28.464
he got into three years ago.

01:28.547 --> 01:30.341
But he didn't hit
Dodge's sister.

01:30.424 --> 01:31.759
No, he couldn't have.

01:31.842 --> 01:33.385
But around the same time,
Luke got busted

01:33.469 --> 01:34.678
boosting a car.

01:34.762 --> 01:37.014
Found a dead girl in the trunk.

01:37.097 --> 01:39.058
Cortez said he could be
on the hook for murder.

01:39.141 --> 01:41.185
I don't think this was ever
about a sting.

01:41.268 --> 01:43.270
I think that he always just
wanted the money.

01:43.354 --> 01:44.939
The other day,
when I was on Luke's boat,

01:45.022 --> 01:47.066
I found some betting slips
when I came looking for you.

01:47.149 --> 01:50.277
And I just found out today that
it was Cortez that was betting.

01:50.361 --> 01:51.946
He was bettin' on Dodge?

01:52.029 --> 01:53.447
Mm-hmm.

01:57.618 --> 01:59.912
So Luke took another beating
for me, huh?

01:59.995 --> 02:01.247
What do you mean?

02:01.330 --> 02:03.415
There's no way Luke would
help Dodge win over me.

02:03.499 --> 02:05.209
This was punishment.

02:07.670 --> 02:10.047
He's the only one
that ever gave a shit about me.

02:12.842 --> 02:15.010
Mm, that's not true.

02:19.056 --> 02:21.267
You're not going
to let Cortez win, are you?

02:21.350 --> 02:23.352
Guess I don't have
much of a choice, do I?

02:24.728 --> 02:26.480
Ray's going to throw
the game tomorrow.

02:26.564 --> 02:28.023
- What?
- He said that

02:28.107 --> 02:29.191
what happened to Luke
is a warning

02:29.275 --> 02:30.734
and that he doesn't want
anyone else to get hurt.

02:30.818 --> 02:32.319
Okay.

02:32.403 --> 02:33.612
That means Cortez
will do anything

02:33.696 --> 02:34.989
to make sure his bets pay off.

02:35.072 --> 02:36.282
And without proof...

02:36.365 --> 02:37.408
But we have proof.

02:37.491 --> 02:38.450
We have the betting slips

02:38.534 --> 02:39.952
and we know
that he lied to Dodge.

02:40.035 --> 02:41.495
He'll just say that we're lying.

02:41.579 --> 02:42.580
That the betting slip was fake.

02:42.663 --> 02:43.914
So let's talk to your dad.

02:43.998 --> 02:45.541
That's my dad's word
against the sheriff's.

02:45.624 --> 02:46.709
I don't like that.

02:46.792 --> 02:48.335
- So we should just let him win?
- No, Heather,

02:48.419 --> 02:50.546
we shouldn't just let him win,
we have to.

02:50.629 --> 02:52.631
He outplayed us.

02:53.757 --> 02:56.218
That's what happens when
you get to write the rules.

02:59.972 --> 03:01.390
[line ringing]

03:01.473 --> 03:03.350
[woman] Auto Trader,
how can I help you?

03:03.434 --> 03:06.395
Hi. Yeah, uh, I'm interested
in selling my car.

03:06.478 --> 03:08.772
I-I was wondering
if you could give me an estimate

03:08.856 --> 03:10.232
on an Audi A4?

03:10.316 --> 03:12.026
It only has 20,000 miles on it.

03:12.109 --> 03:14.194
[woman] Sure,
let's see what we can do.

03:15.863 --> 03:17.865
[entry bells jingle]

03:21.243 --> 03:23.746
I'm so sorry, we're closed.

03:23.829 --> 03:26.707
It's okay, I'm not hungry.

03:26.790 --> 03:28.375
Jessica, right?

03:32.254 --> 03:34.006
I'm Melanie Cortez.

03:34.089 --> 03:36.091
I know who you are.

03:41.430 --> 03:43.641
[sighs]

03:43.724 --> 03:46.185
So I guess you're...

03:46.268 --> 03:49.229
here for some sort of apology?

03:49.313 --> 03:51.357
Yeah.

03:51.440 --> 03:53.651
But not from you.

03:59.615 --> 04:02.952
How far would you go
for your child?

04:05.829 --> 04:08.707
Turns out you're not
the sheriff's only secret.

04:15.798 --> 04:17.925
[Cortez] Jimmy killed himself,

04:18.008 --> 04:19.677
playing a game
of Russian roulette.

04:22.888 --> 04:25.599
[Melanie] He's the one
who switched out the gun.

04:25.683 --> 04:27.726
He killed himself, James.

04:29.436 --> 04:30.938
[Langley] Mary Clark was right.

04:31.021 --> 04:32.564
Someone was blackmailing Abby

04:32.648 --> 04:34.066
to get her out of the game.

04:34.149 --> 04:36.986
But I can't, I can't think of
anyone else besides Jimmy

04:37.069 --> 04:38.988
that could write those notes,
because some of them were

04:39.071 --> 04:40.614
extremely personal.

04:40.698 --> 04:42.241
[Cortez] "Tomorrow
everyone will know

04:42.324 --> 04:43.367
you're a whore.

04:43.450 --> 04:44.410
If you don't quit

04:44.493 --> 04:46.412
they'll know
you killed the baby."

04:46.495 --> 04:47.788
[Williams] What is it, Langley?

04:47.871 --> 04:49.832
What couldn't you tell me
over the phone?

04:49.915 --> 04:51.458
- I did some digging.
- Okay.

04:51.542 --> 04:54.545
And it turns out Cortez
is in severe debt.

04:55.963 --> 04:57.381
Like, last year,

04:57.464 --> 05:00.634
he even took out loans
in Jimmy's name.

05:00.718 --> 05:02.219
[Williams] That explains why
he was in on the gambling ring.

05:02.302 --> 05:03.846
[Langley] Yeah.

05:03.929 --> 05:05.639
And Jimmy knew that.

05:05.723 --> 05:08.267
And he figured out that
his dad was threatening Abby

05:08.350 --> 05:10.811
to get her out of the game.

05:11.895 --> 05:14.565
[Williams] Cortez wrote
those notes?

05:14.648 --> 05:17.609
[Langley] Yeah.
To make sure Jimmy would win.

05:19.361 --> 05:21.363
[Williams] Cortez has
been playing us.

05:21.447 --> 05:22.865
[Langley] He's got to be
manipulating the game again

05:22.948 --> 05:25.576
so he can pay off his debts.

05:25.659 --> 05:27.619
He had us so focused
on last year's game, I...

05:27.703 --> 05:29.538
I don't know what else
he's been hiding.

05:30.956 --> 05:32.833
Well, we got to find out.

05:32.916 --> 05:34.960
[lock clicking]

05:35.044 --> 05:36.587
[keys jangle]

05:46.680 --> 05:49.641
[Anne] So,
what happened last night?

05:50.684 --> 05:53.187
- I, um...
- Come here.

06:04.323 --> 06:06.784
Sheriff Cortez is going
to be here in the morning

06:06.867 --> 06:09.787
to walk the fence
and ask me a lot of questions

06:09.870 --> 06:11.955
about how the tiger escaped

06:12.039 --> 06:14.500
that I'm going to have
to answer with lies.

06:14.583 --> 06:17.044
So I expect the truth from you.

06:17.127 --> 06:20.255
Lily thought that she was

06:20.339 --> 06:22.841
playing a secret game
called Panic.

06:22.925 --> 06:24.259
Right.

06:24.343 --> 06:26.136
The game.

06:31.391 --> 06:33.727
Did Lily hear about Panic
from you?

06:33.811 --> 06:35.020
No.

06:35.104 --> 06:36.271
I really don't know
where she got the idea

06:36.355 --> 06:37.523
- to do some...
- Something

06:37.606 --> 06:39.358
so outrageously stupid.

06:40.609 --> 06:41.777
I'm so sorry, Anne.

06:41.860 --> 06:43.529
Are you playing Panic?

06:43.612 --> 06:45.739
And don't even think
about lying.

06:47.866 --> 06:48.992
No.

06:50.494 --> 06:51.495
Well...

06:53.497 --> 06:55.415
...I'm not anymore.

06:55.499 --> 06:57.042
But you were.

06:57.126 --> 06:59.294
I thought you were smarter
than that.

07:00.963 --> 07:02.756
[Anne sighs]

07:04.341 --> 07:07.261
Here's some advice.

07:07.344 --> 07:10.556
Figure out what it is
that you're really scared of.

07:10.639 --> 07:13.308
Something you can't run or jump

07:13.392 --> 07:15.936
or climb your way out of,
no matter how hard you try.

07:16.979 --> 07:18.647
And when you find that,

07:18.730 --> 07:20.482
you look it straight in the eye.

07:20.566 --> 07:23.026
You walk toward it.

07:23.110 --> 07:24.778
Because if you run,

07:24.862 --> 07:27.114
it will always catch up
with you.

07:27.197 --> 07:29.199
What if this is it?

07:29.283 --> 07:32.369
What if I played Panic
to get out of here?

07:36.039 --> 07:38.667
You know, I'm afraid
that I'll never leave.

07:40.169 --> 07:44.131
And then...
what if that's the ending?

07:47.134 --> 07:50.262
Well, I'd start
by changing your story.

07:56.226 --> 07:57.769
[Dodge] He's using us, Dayna.

07:57.853 --> 07:59.897
[Dayna] You think Cortez lied
to us about Luke

07:59.980 --> 08:01.315
because...

08:01.398 --> 08:03.358
- he has money on your win?
- Yes.

08:03.442 --> 08:04.860
It's the only thing
that makes sense.

08:04.943 --> 08:06.195
My guess is,

08:06.278 --> 08:08.739
is that he's gonna
let Luke get all the blame

08:08.822 --> 08:10.532
after he walks away
with the winnings.

08:10.616 --> 08:11.825
Wait, I, uh...

08:11.909 --> 08:13.619
Joust is tomorrow.
What are you gonna do?

08:14.745 --> 08:16.830
I'm gonna let Cortez drive.

08:16.914 --> 08:18.373
♪ ♪

08:18.457 --> 08:20.209
Wait, so you're gonna
let him win all that money?

08:20.292 --> 08:21.752
No, I'm not going
to let him win,

08:21.835 --> 08:23.545
but I can at least let him
think that he's going to.

08:23.629 --> 08:25.797
[Dayna] But... how?

08:25.881 --> 08:27.549
Don't worry.

08:27.633 --> 08:28.800
I got this.

08:28.884 --> 08:31.345
- Dodge...
- I'll see you.

08:31.428 --> 08:33.680
- D-Dodge!
- [door opens and closes]

08:35.265 --> 08:37.267
♪ ♪

08:54.076 --> 08:55.786
Joust signal went up.

08:55.869 --> 08:57.829
You and me.

08:57.913 --> 09:00.457
Bet you been waiting all summer,
ain't ya?

09:00.540 --> 09:02.376
Longer than that.

09:08.674 --> 09:11.760
Look...

09:11.843 --> 09:14.805
I'm sorry for what happened
to your sister.

09:14.888 --> 09:16.473
But it wasn't my brother
that hit her.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.433
I know, Ray.

09:18.517 --> 09:20.686
You know?

09:20.769 --> 09:23.730
Natalie showed me
the police reports.

09:23.814 --> 09:26.066
- I know Cortez was lying.
- Well,

09:26.149 --> 09:27.609
don't take it personal.

09:27.693 --> 09:29.695
Seems like there's a whole lot
of that going on.

09:29.778 --> 09:31.363
Well, tonight's our chance
we can end it all.

09:31.446 --> 09:32.406
What do you mean?

09:32.489 --> 09:34.783
Cortez is going to be driving

09:34.866 --> 09:36.868
my car at Joust.

09:38.120 --> 09:39.496
He really needs the win
and I have a plan

09:39.579 --> 09:40.914
that'll make sure
that he doesn't get it.

09:40.998 --> 09:43.125
- Well, I'm listening.
- No.

09:43.208 --> 09:44.334
Not here.

09:45.711 --> 09:46.878
[sighs]

09:48.797 --> 09:49.881
Fine.

09:49.965 --> 09:52.801
Boatyard, 9:00 p.m.

09:52.884 --> 09:55.137
[footsteps receding]

09:55.220 --> 09:56.805
[horse whinnies]

09:56.888 --> 09:58.307
[Cortez] Your boss is
all broken up

09:58.390 --> 09:59.391
about that tiger, huh?

09:59.474 --> 10:00.559
Mm-hmm.

10:00.642 --> 10:02.227
Ms. Nill, how long have you

10:02.311 --> 10:04.021
and your sister Lily been
living in this house?

10:04.104 --> 10:05.647
I told you, remember?

10:05.731 --> 10:07.441
We're just house-sitting.

10:07.524 --> 10:09.026
And she can't sleep
in a bed without me.

10:09.109 --> 10:12.029
You guys have gotten
pretty cozy for, uh...

10:12.112 --> 10:14.323
only house-sitting
for a couple days.

10:14.406 --> 10:16.491
Anne didn't know how long
she'd be gone.

10:16.575 --> 10:19.119
You know, I hear you all
have gotten a couple visits

10:19.202 --> 10:21.788
from Child Protective Services.

10:21.872 --> 10:23.665
If you're having trouble
at home,

10:23.749 --> 10:25.459
you can tell me.

10:28.253 --> 10:31.214
Thank you, but... no trouble.

10:31.298 --> 10:32.716
That's good to hear.

10:32.799 --> 10:34.509
- Mm-hmm.
- I think you and I

10:34.593 --> 10:36.887
can both agree that we've had
plenty of trouble around here

10:36.970 --> 10:38.930
- this summer, right?
- Oh, for sure.

10:39.014 --> 10:43.685
You know, Ms. Nill...
you're almost grown.

10:43.769 --> 10:45.687
But your sister Lily,

10:45.771 --> 10:48.398
she's just a kid,
and kids are vulnerable.

10:48.482 --> 10:51.026
They need to be protected.

10:51.109 --> 10:52.444
They need a safe place
to grow up.

10:52.527 --> 10:53.653
They need a safe home,
and I want

10:53.737 --> 10:55.238
to make sure that she's got one.

10:57.032 --> 11:00.786
You would never gamble with
your sister's life, would you?

11:00.869 --> 11:03.121
No.

11:03.205 --> 11:04.581
Good.

11:05.874 --> 11:07.667
Y'all be careful.

11:07.751 --> 11:09.878
There's a tiger on the loose.

11:09.961 --> 11:11.838
[exhales]

11:29.731 --> 11:31.483
Thanks for coming over so quick.

11:31.566 --> 11:32.943
His phone kept going off
in his bedroom,

11:33.026 --> 11:34.611
and I thought it was weird
he left it behind.

11:34.694 --> 11:37.364
And then I... I saw the rope.

11:39.408 --> 11:41.952
It was our dad's
favorite bull rope.

11:42.035 --> 11:43.870
I wanted to burn it.

11:43.954 --> 11:47.541
Dodge told me about him.

11:50.168 --> 11:52.337
Dodge was the one
that found him, you know.

11:52.421 --> 11:55.132
After he killed himself.

11:55.215 --> 11:57.717
This is a message.

11:57.801 --> 12:00.137
What's he trying to say?

12:00.220 --> 12:02.389
Dodge said he was going
to meet up with Ray tonight

12:02.472 --> 12:04.516
to figure things out.
He won't let Cortez win,

12:04.599 --> 12:10.856
but... I'm worried
he's planning something awful.

12:16.278 --> 12:18.238
[Ray] So tell me again
how this is supposed to work.

12:18.321 --> 12:20.198
Cortez is picking up my car
in a half hour.

12:20.282 --> 12:21.741
And then he's going to Joust.

12:21.825 --> 12:24.286
And I want your truck
so I can drive up against him.

12:24.369 --> 12:25.662
You want to borrow my car
'cause you think

12:25.745 --> 12:26.955
I'm gonna blow the game
and let him win?

12:27.038 --> 12:28.874
Won't you?

12:28.957 --> 12:30.667
My brother's in the hospital.

12:30.750 --> 12:31.835
My sister will never walk again.

12:31.918 --> 12:33.003
Cortez didn't do that to her.

12:33.086 --> 12:34.379
No, you're right,
but he made sure

12:34.463 --> 12:36.006
that we wouldn't
find out whoever did.

12:37.090 --> 12:38.383
Then it looks like
we're at a draw.

12:38.467 --> 12:39.551
Ray, we're not at a draw.

12:39.634 --> 12:40.969
You're giving me
your car keys, okay?

12:41.052 --> 12:41.970
- Why?
- Ray.

12:42.053 --> 12:43.346
Are you gonna drive into
him at Joust?

12:43.430 --> 12:44.598
- Is that your big plan?
- Ray, give me

12:44.681 --> 12:45.891
your fucking keys, okay?

12:45.974 --> 12:48.935
- [branch snaps]
- [wings fluttering]

12:50.145 --> 12:51.563
Did you tell Cortez

12:51.646 --> 12:54.441
- where we were going?
- You think I'm fucking stupid?

12:56.109 --> 12:57.694
Listen.

12:57.777 --> 12:59.237
Let's split up.

12:59.321 --> 13:02.657
Can't catch both of us
at the same time.

13:02.741 --> 13:05.076
♪ ♪

13:07.537 --> 13:10.290
[Bishop] Are you sure you
don't want to come tonight?

13:10.373 --> 13:12.209
Yeah, we know Ray's gonna
forfeit. What's the point?

13:12.292 --> 13:15.045
The point is,
I leave in two days.

13:17.923 --> 13:20.175
Come on, Heather. I...

13:20.258 --> 13:22.052
I'm coming home
for Thanksgiving.

13:22.135 --> 13:25.180
Things will be different.

13:25.263 --> 13:27.057
- We will be different.
- Yeah.

13:27.140 --> 13:29.809
We'll be different.
But we'll still be us.

13:29.893 --> 13:31.853
[Heather] And I'll
still be stuck here.

13:31.937 --> 13:33.939
Hmm.

13:34.022 --> 13:36.900
- [sighs]
- [phone vibrates]

13:36.983 --> 13:38.818
Oh, shit. I got to change.

13:38.902 --> 13:41.738
Hunt and Leela are coming to
get me in, like, 20 minutes.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.074
Where's your car?

13:44.157 --> 13:47.744
Uh, I, uh, I left it
in the shop.

13:59.256 --> 14:01.341
You okay?

14:03.677 --> 14:06.012
If people like Cortez

14:06.096 --> 14:09.182
can get away
with doing terrible things,

14:09.266 --> 14:12.269
and there's nothing
we can do to stop them...

14:15.397 --> 14:18.233
...what's the point
of doing anything at all?

14:18.316 --> 14:20.443
What's the point of caring?

14:22.612 --> 14:26.658
I... I guess you've got
to pick your battles.

14:26.741 --> 14:29.119
Know when the odds
are stacked against you.

14:29.202 --> 14:32.622
But what if they're always
stacked the same way?

14:33.832 --> 14:37.836
Then, for the things you really,
really care about,

14:37.919 --> 14:41.756
or care about changing,
I guess you take the risk.

14:45.218 --> 14:47.137
[insects trilling]

14:47.220 --> 14:49.222
♪ ♪

14:55.103 --> 14:57.856
[soft clattering nearby]

15:01.318 --> 15:03.862
- [metallic clang]
- Shit.

15:09.451 --> 15:10.702
[grunts]

15:19.210 --> 15:21.004
[unzips bag]

15:22.297 --> 15:23.923
[paper rustling]

15:25.634 --> 15:27.135
What the fuck?

15:40.315 --> 15:43.985
Lily? Lily!

15:44.069 --> 15:46.404
I need to talk to you.

15:46.488 --> 15:48.031
Come here. Look at me.

15:48.114 --> 15:50.825
I know you were supposed to
keep that invitation a secret.

15:50.909 --> 15:53.620
But I found another one, and
this one is from the sheriff.

15:53.703 --> 15:55.538
So, is that who gave it to you?

16:00.460 --> 16:04.297
He told me I could help you
win Panic if I played, too.

16:04.381 --> 16:05.715
He made me swear not to tell.

16:05.799 --> 16:09.219
What do you mean, help me win?

16:09.302 --> 16:11.262
When did he give you that note?

16:11.346 --> 16:14.224
[Lily] Before the sleepover.

16:14.307 --> 16:17.060
[Heather] So this was
about my individual challenge.

16:20.063 --> 16:21.773
Nat, are you at Joust?

16:21.856 --> 16:23.233
[Natalie] No,
I'm actually at Ray's.

16:23.316 --> 16:25.235
What? Why?

16:25.318 --> 16:27.195
I'm looking for Dodge.
I was worried about him.

16:27.278 --> 16:28.446
[Heather] Where's Dodge?

16:28.530 --> 16:30.198
I... I don't know.

16:30.281 --> 16:33.368
Dayna told me that Ray and Dodge
had some plan to stop Cortez.

16:33.451 --> 16:35.370
But, Heather...

16:35.453 --> 16:38.790
she said that Cortez will be
driving Dodge's car at Joust.

16:38.873 --> 16:41.167
What the fuck?

16:41.251 --> 16:43.795
Cortez is at Joust?

16:43.878 --> 16:45.797
- Does Ray know?
- His truck is still here.

16:45.880 --> 16:48.967
Jesus. All right, what if...

16:49.050 --> 16:50.593
what if Cortez has decided

16:50.677 --> 16:51.803
to get Ray and Dodge
out of the way?

16:51.886 --> 16:54.848
[panting] Call your dad.

16:54.931 --> 16:57.350
Say it's an emergency.
Say whatever you want, okay?

16:57.434 --> 16:58.351
All right.

16:58.435 --> 17:01.688
This has to end tonight.

17:04.274 --> 17:06.526
[♪ Ashnikko: "Tantrum"]

17:06.609 --> 17:09.446
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

17:16.369 --> 17:17.662
♪ Throw a tantrum ♪

17:17.746 --> 17:20.331
♪ Ooh, sorry, Mom and Dad ♪

17:20.415 --> 17:22.041
[laughs] Yeah!

17:23.084 --> 17:26.087
♪ I did something bad ♪

17:26.171 --> 17:27.672
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

17:27.756 --> 17:29.466
♪ Please don't get attached ♪

17:29.549 --> 17:30.717
♪ There's no coming back...

17:30.800 --> 17:32.469
[laughter]

17:32.552 --> 17:34.012
[Summer] Phones, please.

17:34.095 --> 17:36.306
One for you.
No pictures, no videos.

17:36.389 --> 17:39.184
♪ Baby, doll me up
'cause I'm a brat...

17:39.267 --> 17:40.685
- Hey, there she is.
- Hey.

17:40.769 --> 17:41.811
♪ Demi-devil...

17:41.895 --> 17:43.104
Phones, please.

17:43.188 --> 17:44.230
[in distance] ♪ Bitch,
I am one ♪

17:44.314 --> 17:46.566
♪ Throw a tantrum ♪♪

17:48.651 --> 17:50.653
♪ ♪

17:53.156 --> 17:55.241
- [static crackles]
- Dodge is here!

17:55.325 --> 17:57.035
He just pulled up
to the start gate.

17:58.286 --> 18:00.413
[lighter flicks]

18:04.125 --> 18:05.627
Troy, what about Ray?

18:06.669 --> 18:08.254
Not yet.

18:08.338 --> 18:10.340
♪ ♪

18:16.930 --> 18:18.681
[engine turns off]

18:27.148 --> 18:30.109
Come on, where are they?

18:32.153 --> 18:33.154
Yes.

18:37.158 --> 18:38.952
[engine starts]

18:39.035 --> 18:40.578
[indistinct radio chatter]

18:40.662 --> 18:42.205
Well, any luck?

18:42.288 --> 18:43.665
You know, I appreciate
the information.

18:43.748 --> 18:45.500
Thank you very much.

18:45.583 --> 18:47.961
Maybe. Neighbor quarter mile
down from the Halls

18:48.044 --> 18:49.295
said that there's a boat,

18:49.379 --> 18:50.880
matching the description
of Ray's,

18:50.964 --> 18:52.215
idling in the middle
of the river.

18:52.298 --> 18:53.842
[engine revving]

18:58.972 --> 19:00.974
♪ ♪

19:02.183 --> 19:03.893
[Ray exhales]

19:08.773 --> 19:11.609
[Dodge inhales sharply, groans]

19:11.693 --> 19:13.111
[Ray] There he is.

19:13.194 --> 19:15.905
There's my guy.

19:15.989 --> 19:17.866
Goddamn it, Ray,
I'm gonna kill you!

19:17.949 --> 19:20.326
Oh, come on.
Get a hobby.

19:20.410 --> 19:21.703
Did Cortez put you up to this?

19:21.786 --> 19:23.121
No. Right about now,

19:23.204 --> 19:24.789
he should be
on the road to Joust.

19:24.873 --> 19:26.708
- Isn't that what you wanted?
- No! I wanted to

19:26.791 --> 19:27.709
go up against him, you moron.

19:27.792 --> 19:30.378
[Ray] I know, I'm sorry.

19:30.461 --> 19:33.423
Couldn't let you do that.

19:33.506 --> 19:35.717
I couldn't let you do that
to my truck.

19:35.800 --> 19:38.011
Technically,

19:38.094 --> 19:40.013
you should be thanking me.

19:40.096 --> 19:41.764
I saved your fucking life.

19:41.848 --> 19:43.474
I didn't ask for your help.

19:43.558 --> 19:45.852
Who says I was helping you?

19:45.935 --> 19:48.062
I do have a question
for you, though.

19:48.146 --> 19:52.275
Were you really planning on
blowing yourself up with Cortez?

19:52.358 --> 19:53.985
Or is that bomb under my car

19:54.068 --> 19:55.987
just a little
Christmas decoration?

20:00.700 --> 20:02.327
I wish Ray would
fucking hurry up.

20:02.410 --> 20:03.786
[Sarah] Yeah.

20:03.870 --> 20:04.829
[line ringing]

20:04.913 --> 20:05.914
[Ray] This is Ray,
leave a message.

20:05.997 --> 20:09.083
♪ You wanna take us? ♪

20:09.167 --> 20:10.543
♪ We don't wanna ride
for free...

20:10.627 --> 20:13.504
All right, guys. I know
y'all were hoping for a show,

20:13.588 --> 20:16.215
but it's looking like Ray Hall
is no-showing.

20:16.299 --> 20:18.426
- [booing]
- No, he still has two minutes.

20:18.509 --> 20:19.928
Two minutes, everyone.

20:20.011 --> 20:22.221
- Where the fuck is Ray?
- He's still not picking up.

20:22.305 --> 20:23.681
Where the fuck is he?

20:23.765 --> 20:25.308
You think he's okay?

20:25.391 --> 20:27.101
Maybe he's with Luke.

20:27.185 --> 20:29.145
If something happened,
he would have called.

20:30.438 --> 20:33.107
I never thought Ray Hall
would just not show up.

20:33.191 --> 20:34.943
Maybe he didn't have a choice.

20:37.153 --> 20:40.239
Come on, man. Where are you?

20:51.584 --> 20:53.836
Let's call it,
he's obviously not coming.

20:53.920 --> 20:55.838
[others protesting]

20:55.922 --> 20:57.173
All right, um...

20:58.424 --> 21:02.929
By virtue of forfeit
of the right to compete,

21:03.012 --> 21:05.473
the winner of Panic is...

21:05.556 --> 21:07.725
[horn honking]

21:07.809 --> 21:09.143
He's here.

21:12.981 --> 21:14.899
Wait!

21:14.983 --> 21:17.151
- [over walkie] He just
pulled up to the gate.
- Wait, Ray's here.

21:17.235 --> 21:19.445
- Ray Hall is here.
- No fucking way!

21:19.529 --> 21:21.239
[all cheering]

21:26.995 --> 21:28.997
[panting]

21:33.251 --> 21:35.503
[Diggins] Ladies and gentlemen,

21:35.586 --> 21:37.755
boys and girls,

21:37.839 --> 21:41.134
welcome to the final challenge!

21:41.217 --> 21:44.220
- Yeah!
- [all cheering]

21:45.430 --> 21:47.432
[panting]

21:49.350 --> 21:52.145
Tonight's challenge will be
winner takes all.

21:52.228 --> 21:55.815
No points, no privileges,
and no wiggle room,

21:55.898 --> 21:58.860
both figuratively
and literally.

21:58.943 --> 22:01.821
[Ray] You ain't the only
family tragedy in this town.

22:01.904 --> 22:05.825
Shit, you ain't even the only
family tragedy on this boat.

22:05.908 --> 22:08.911
That's why...

22:08.995 --> 22:10.538
you don't get to hog
all the family revenge.

22:10.621 --> 22:11.748
What are you talking about?

22:11.831 --> 22:13.291
Do you really think
I'd let somebody

22:13.374 --> 22:14.667
bash my brother's skull in

22:14.751 --> 22:15.793
and let 'em walk away
with a payday?

22:15.877 --> 22:17.086
Well, since we're on a boat

22:17.170 --> 22:18.838
in the middle
of the goddamn lake,

22:18.921 --> 22:20.923
letting him win, yeah,
it kind of looks like that.

22:21.007 --> 22:22.175
It sure does, doesn't it?

22:22.258 --> 22:24.343
That's what makes it so genius.

22:24.427 --> 22:26.345
[chuckles]

22:26.429 --> 22:28.973
Too bad he'll only have
about 20 minutes to enjoy

22:29.057 --> 22:32.810
his sweet taste of victory
before the bomb goes off.

22:32.894 --> 22:36.981
Give it up
for our final contestants,

22:37.065 --> 22:40.485
Ray Hall and Dodge Mason!

22:40.568 --> 22:42.904
[cheering and applause]

22:42.987 --> 22:46.491
- [Diggins] Game's on!
- Little son of a bitch.

22:48.659 --> 22:50.328
Ray, the bomb's in your truck.

22:50.411 --> 22:53.122
It was.
[snickers]

22:53.206 --> 22:55.041
Now it's in yours.

22:55.124 --> 22:57.293
What are you talking about?

22:58.294 --> 23:00.671
After you told me
Cortez was gonna be

23:00.755 --> 23:02.048
driving your car at Joust,

23:02.131 --> 23:03.800
I went ahead and took
the liberty

23:03.883 --> 23:05.551
of taking the bomb
out of my car

23:05.635 --> 23:07.261
and placing it
under your bumper.

23:09.138 --> 23:11.557
I'm so sorry about your car.

23:11.641 --> 23:14.977
The good news is, you're
officially the winner of Panic.

23:15.061 --> 23:19.232
The bad news is,
at around 12:20,

23:19.315 --> 23:22.068
you're gonna have to find
somebody else to hate.

23:22.151 --> 23:26.656
[revving engine]

23:26.739 --> 23:29.784
A quick reminder to everyone
watching tonight.

23:29.867 --> 23:32.078
From now until we call it,

23:32.161 --> 23:35.331
no one leaves the hill.
Okay?

23:35.414 --> 23:36.958
Nadie.

23:37.041 --> 23:40.461
Dodge!
Dodge?

23:40.545 --> 23:43.464
I'm so happy you're okay.

23:43.548 --> 23:46.843
Hey. Hey, I thought
something terrible happened.

23:46.926 --> 23:48.553
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Stop, stop, stop, stop.

23:51.514 --> 23:54.892
Wait, Ray.
If you're here, then...

23:54.976 --> 23:56.435
what's your truck doing
at Joust?

23:56.519 --> 23:59.063
- Bishop said you're there.
- What?

23:59.147 --> 24:01.482
What the fuck?

24:01.566 --> 24:02.775
Whose fucking truck is this?

24:02.859 --> 24:05.528
It's Anne's.
Oh, fuck.

24:05.611 --> 24:06.821
What?

24:06.904 --> 24:09.699
Heather's at Joust.
Let's fucking go.

24:12.451 --> 24:14.745
Signals on.

24:14.829 --> 24:16.664
[cheering and applause]

24:16.747 --> 24:19.667
[engine revving]

24:24.380 --> 24:26.507
Three...

24:31.429 --> 24:33.097
- ...two...
- Wait.

24:38.895 --> 24:39.937
...one...

24:40.021 --> 24:42.106
Wait. No! Stop, stop.
Stop the game!

24:46.194 --> 24:47.195
Stop the game!

24:53.201 --> 24:54.493
- No.
- Bishop.

24:59.624 --> 25:00.917
There's a bomb.
We got to stop her.

25:03.836 --> 25:06.255
♪ ♪

25:13.054 --> 25:14.931
[breathing deeply]

25:34.700 --> 25:36.953
♪ ♪

25:42.083 --> 25:43.834
[whimpers]

25:43.918 --> 25:45.503
[growls]

25:45.586 --> 25:48.798
[tires screeching]

26:13.614 --> 26:14.824
Oh, my God, Dodge.

26:14.907 --> 26:16.909
[woman] Dodge was in there.

26:16.993 --> 26:19.578
[panting]

26:19.662 --> 26:21.122
What's Heather doing
in Ray's truck?

26:21.205 --> 26:22.957
And where the fuck is Ray?

26:39.140 --> 26:41.475
[grunting]

26:41.559 --> 26:42.810
[groaning]

26:42.893 --> 26:44.895
[beeping]

26:52.069 --> 26:54.196
[Heather] Once upon a time
there was a girl who believed

26:54.280 --> 26:57.742
learning to fly meant she could
escape her own shadow.

26:57.825 --> 26:59.452
Diggins, that's a fucking tiger.

26:59.535 --> 27:01.037
[woman] Holy crap, it's a tiger.

27:04.790 --> 27:08.502
[Heather] So she jumped,
hoping to grow wings.

27:08.586 --> 27:12.256
She ran, hoping
to outrace the ground.

27:12.340 --> 27:14.091
But there was no escaping
her shadow.

27:14.175 --> 27:15.468
[growling softly]

27:15.551 --> 27:18.304
So the girl finally stopped
and turned to meet it.

27:18.387 --> 27:22.391
And the girl's shadow, afraid,

27:22.475 --> 27:23.809
laid down at her feet,

27:23.893 --> 27:26.645
amazed at her power
to stand up.

27:28.356 --> 27:31.192
[breathing heavily]

27:31.275 --> 27:32.943
[beeps]

27:36.655 --> 27:38.991
- [roars]
- [panicked shouting]

27:42.411 --> 27:43.788
Oh, my God. Dodge.

27:43.871 --> 27:45.456
- [panicked cries continue]
- Heather!

27:46.499 --> 27:48.417
Heather, Heather, Heather.

27:48.501 --> 27:49.668
- Hey, hey, are you okay?
- [siren wailing]

27:49.752 --> 27:51.212
- Mm-hmm.
- Are you okay?

27:59.011 --> 28:01.680
- I need Fire and EMS
at Phantom Hill Road.
- Heather! Heather!

28:01.764 --> 28:03.808
What the hell is
wrong with you?

28:03.891 --> 28:05.601
I'm sorry, guys.

28:05.684 --> 28:07.686
[man] Hey, look. Dodge.

28:07.770 --> 28:09.480
[woman] Is that Dodge?

28:09.563 --> 28:12.024
[indistinct chatter]

28:13.275 --> 28:15.611
[woman] Dodge!

28:29.250 --> 28:32.128
♪ ♪

28:57.278 --> 28:59.864
[breathing heavily]

29:10.040 --> 29:12.751
[tiger growling]

29:16.464 --> 29:18.340
[rifle cocks]

29:19.467 --> 29:20.801
Melanie?

29:33.230 --> 29:35.232
[tiger growls]

29:50.873 --> 29:52.416
[engine starts]

29:53.834 --> 29:57.213
- Is he...?
- Dead. We need
to get out of here.

30:06.388 --> 30:08.849
[tiger growls softly]

30:14.897 --> 30:19.527
[Heather] Anyone can play Panic,
but only one person can win.

30:19.610 --> 30:22.446
Everyone else walks away
a loser.

30:22.530 --> 30:25.616
That's why Panic is a game
about fear,

30:25.699 --> 30:27.451
but not in the way we think.

30:28.869 --> 30:31.539
To beat the game, you have
to set the challenges yourself.

30:31.622 --> 30:34.708
To win the game,
you have to believe in something

30:34.792 --> 30:36.710
worth the risk.

30:38.379 --> 30:42.633
The opposite of fear
isn't courage, it's believing.

30:42.716 --> 30:46.220
And finding something
worth believing in.

30:46.303 --> 30:49.848
Yourself is a good place
to start.

30:49.932 --> 30:54.186
Luckily, you can find that
anywhere,

30:54.270 --> 30:56.981
even in the middle
of Nowhere, Texas.

31:03.571 --> 31:06.782
[woman speaks indistinctly
over P.A.]

31:06.865 --> 31:08.325
[Ray] Look.

31:09.910 --> 31:10.828
There.

31:10.911 --> 31:14.748
[monitor beeping]

31:14.832 --> 31:17.293
You see that?
Right there.

31:17.376 --> 31:19.753
Two days ago
he couldn't even blink.

31:19.837 --> 31:22.631
It's like the doctor said,
he's a real fighter.

31:22.715 --> 31:24.174
[Ray] Stubborn as hell.

31:24.258 --> 31:25.634
Wouldn't make much
of a difference

31:25.718 --> 31:27.761
if you were brain-dead,
though, would it, fucko?

31:36.687 --> 31:38.981
[laughs softly]

31:39.064 --> 31:40.441
He gave me the finger.

31:40.524 --> 31:42.776
[both laughing]

31:44.820 --> 31:46.280
He gave me the finger.

31:49.158 --> 31:51.076
My fucking brother, man.

31:54.330 --> 31:56.790
[Natalie] Hey, remember to wear
your flip-flops in the shower.

31:56.874 --> 31:58.000
[laughter]

31:58.083 --> 31:59.668
Um, remember to take
pictures of the library.

31:59.752 --> 32:02.713
[Bishop] Wow. You are truly
a staggering nerd.

32:02.796 --> 32:04.214
Mm, I wouldn't if I were you.

32:04.298 --> 32:06.508
She might kill you off
in the novel.

32:06.592 --> 32:08.510
- I told you, it's fiction.
- Oh, yeah.

32:08.594 --> 32:11.180
A totally fictional novel
about a nowhere town

32:11.263 --> 32:14.558
where a group of teens play
a scary game every summer?

32:14.642 --> 32:16.226
[Heather] They're not teens,
they're ghosts.

32:16.310 --> 32:19.229
[Natalie] Oh, that's right,
they're ghost teens. Yeah.

32:21.523 --> 32:23.192
You have to FaceTime us
every day.

32:23.275 --> 32:24.943
Minimum.

32:25.027 --> 32:28.489
I will, I-I promise.

32:28.572 --> 32:29.990
[phone vibrates]

32:30.074 --> 32:32.618
Oh, shit, uh, I-I got to go.

32:32.701 --> 32:33.911
- Oh.
- My dad's...

32:33.994 --> 32:36.121
- Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah. So...

32:39.249 --> 32:41.585
Look, uh, don't cry.
If you cry, I'm gonna cry.

32:41.669 --> 32:43.420
If you cry, I'll laugh.

32:43.504 --> 32:44.630
[Natalie] [laughs] Well,
now you're gonna

32:44.713 --> 32:46.048
get me started.

32:46.131 --> 32:47.633
[Bishop] I'm really gonna
miss you guys.

32:52.763 --> 32:54.640
[Natalie] I swear,
if I ever find out

32:54.723 --> 32:56.809
what happened to the bagman
and the winning pot...

32:56.892 --> 32:59.061
[Heather] Forget the money.
I'm just happy it's over.

32:59.144 --> 33:01.230
[Natalie] You're a hero,
Heather. You know that, right?

33:01.313 --> 33:03.065
[Heather] I was just doing it
for Lily.

33:03.148 --> 33:05.442
Promise me you won't tell anyone
that I was a judge.

33:05.526 --> 33:06.777
[laughs] No.

33:08.612 --> 33:11.782
I had to say those things
on the bridge, Heather.

33:11.865 --> 33:14.618
Otherwise the other judge would
think I was helping you win.

33:14.702 --> 33:16.453
You tipped off Diggins
about cheating at Spurlock's

33:16.537 --> 33:18.288
so I could get to final four.

33:18.372 --> 33:20.124
That's why
you can't tell anyone.

33:20.207 --> 33:22.251
You're not gonna pick
anyone for next year, right?

33:22.334 --> 33:24.545
No, my job here is done.

33:24.628 --> 33:26.380
[laughs] Oh.

33:26.463 --> 33:29.508
Check your e-mail.
I got you a surprise.

33:29.591 --> 33:31.009
[Heather] Very mysterious,
but okay.

33:31.093 --> 33:32.761
Trust me, you'll like it.

33:39.226 --> 33:40.519
Ten steps per answer, huh?

33:41.854 --> 33:43.689
Seems like a fair deal.

33:43.772 --> 33:46.150
So, what do you want
to know about Heather?

33:46.233 --> 33:49.153
You want to know
if she's a good kisser?

33:49.236 --> 33:52.030
Where she likes it
when you touch her?

33:52.114 --> 33:55.909
[Diggins] Come on, Ray. Everyone
knows you hooked up this summer.

33:55.993 --> 33:57.327
[Ray] Then why ask?

33:57.411 --> 33:58.537
And why the fuck
do you think I'd tell you?

33:58.620 --> 34:00.038
[Diggins] 'Cause
the clock's ticking

34:00.122 --> 34:02.291
and the judges want
to know the truth?

34:02.374 --> 34:04.084
Are you in love with her?

34:05.836 --> 34:11.216
See, some beautiful's
nice to look at.

34:11.300 --> 34:14.470
But there's some beautiful,

34:14.553 --> 34:18.182
some beautiful makes you feel
like you're flying.

34:18.265 --> 34:20.976
And it hurts.

34:21.059 --> 34:26.023
'Cause for a second, you forget
that it's leaving you behind.

34:27.775 --> 34:29.485
[Diggins] Still haven't
answered the question.

34:29.568 --> 34:30.819
[Ray] Yes, I have.

34:30.903 --> 34:32.529
I'm a Hall.

34:34.531 --> 34:36.492
I'm deadweight.

34:40.704 --> 34:43.957
And that's bad news
to a girl with wings.

34:49.671 --> 34:50.881
[computer chimes]

34:55.594 --> 34:56.970
[exhales]

35:03.685 --> 35:06.438
"After careful review, this
year's judgment has awarded you

35:06.522 --> 35:08.440
the winning pot."

35:08.524 --> 35:10.609
Holy shit, I won?

35:15.322 --> 35:17.324
[laughs]

35:20.869 --> 35:23.413
♪ I hear them whisper secrets ♪

35:23.497 --> 35:25.791
♪ Till my name is dirt ♪

35:25.874 --> 35:28.460
♪ But I will not falter ♪

35:28.544 --> 35:30.712
♪ I will hide the hurt ♪

35:30.796 --> 35:32.422
[Natalie] Hey.

35:32.506 --> 35:33.507
♪ And I can feel the earth...

35:33.590 --> 35:35.175
Hi.

35:35.259 --> 35:37.427
I'm glad you reached out.

35:37.511 --> 35:38.554
[Dodge] Well,
I'm glad you made it.

35:38.637 --> 35:40.639
[laughs softly] Yep.

35:41.849 --> 35:43.642
♪ Oh, the wind blows...

35:43.725 --> 35:45.352
I wanted to thank you.

35:45.435 --> 35:49.940
The evidence you gave us, it's
giving my family some peace.

35:50.023 --> 35:53.235
- Dodge, that's...
that's amazing.
- Yeah.

35:55.487 --> 35:57.030
You still thinking about L.A.?

35:57.114 --> 35:59.074
[Natalie] Yeah, if my dad ever
lets me leave the county again.

35:59.157 --> 36:02.119
What about you?

36:02.202 --> 36:03.495
What are you gonna do?

36:05.873 --> 36:08.000
Well, after this summer,

36:08.083 --> 36:10.002
- um...
- Yeah.

36:13.422 --> 36:15.424
The truth is...

36:20.012 --> 36:22.556
...I was holding on to so much.

36:22.639 --> 36:26.435
I was so consumed
about what had happened

36:26.518 --> 36:28.312
that I was never thinking
about what was next.

36:28.395 --> 36:31.565
I don't even think I cared
if there was anything at all.

36:31.648 --> 36:33.150
[Natalie] I'm with you on that.

36:33.233 --> 36:37.738
I always thought I could
make sense of everything.

36:37.821 --> 36:41.116
My mom, I mean,
like why she left.

36:41.199 --> 36:43.285
Why I wasn't worth
sticking around for.

36:43.368 --> 36:45.203
But something's different.

36:45.287 --> 36:47.456
I mean, I'm...

36:47.539 --> 36:51.335
I'm still going to L.A.,
I'm just going for myself.

36:53.837 --> 36:57.507
I just think I need to take off.

36:57.591 --> 37:01.386
You know?
Um, drive around awhile.

37:01.470 --> 37:04.097
See what's out there
before I figure out what's next.

37:04.181 --> 37:05.432
- Cool.
- Yeah.

37:05.515 --> 37:07.893
It might be nice to,
to not have a plan.

37:07.976 --> 37:09.227
[both chuckle]

37:09.311 --> 37:11.897
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah, I get that.

37:11.980 --> 37:14.399
[Natalie] So,
what are you gonna do?

37:14.483 --> 37:16.902
[Dodge] Well, I did need
to get a new ride.

37:16.985 --> 37:19.363
[laughs] Oh, I see. Okay.

37:19.446 --> 37:21.531
- What do you think?
- Uh...

37:21.615 --> 37:23.283
- Not bad.
- Yeah?

37:23.367 --> 37:25.410
Yeah.

37:26.954 --> 37:28.497
Well, Dodge Mason,

37:28.580 --> 37:30.749
if you're ever out west,
you got my number.

37:30.832 --> 37:32.876
♪ In the darkest hour ♪

37:32.960 --> 37:34.252
Yeah.

37:34.336 --> 37:36.254
♪ I'll spark a flame...

37:36.338 --> 37:38.090
Take care of yourself.

37:38.173 --> 37:40.008
[laughs softly]

37:40.092 --> 37:41.426
You, too.

37:41.510 --> 37:44.096
♪ In the darkest hour ♪

37:44.179 --> 37:46.098
♪ You'll know my name ♪

37:46.181 --> 37:48.517
♪ I will hold the power ♪

37:48.600 --> 37:50.018
[engine starts]

37:50.102 --> 37:51.937
♪ And I'll run that game ♪

38:04.449 --> 38:05.575
[Ray] Hey.

38:05.659 --> 38:08.120
Winning looks good on you.

38:08.203 --> 38:10.330
You know, I think
there should be a word

38:10.414 --> 38:12.541
for something that's beautiful
but it makes you happy

38:12.624 --> 38:14.710
and sad at the same time.

38:16.712 --> 38:19.131
Yeah. Yeah, there should.

38:30.225 --> 38:32.978
I saw your video.
From the train bridge.

38:33.061 --> 38:35.063
Someone leaked it to me.

38:52.831 --> 38:54.458
I'm scared.

38:55.792 --> 38:57.586
Of what?

38:59.838 --> 39:02.799
Everything.

39:02.883 --> 39:04.301
[laughs softly]

39:06.887 --> 39:08.764
I thought...

39:08.847 --> 39:12.809
for some reason I wouldn't be.

39:12.893 --> 39:16.229
You know, 'cause I played Panic.

39:16.313 --> 39:20.776
♪ They built a tower,
I climbed so high ♪

39:20.859 --> 39:23.070
♪ I could almost reach it...

39:24.112 --> 39:26.031
You know what scares me most?

39:26.114 --> 39:29.076
♪ So damn your love...

39:29.159 --> 39:31.078
You.

39:31.161 --> 39:34.581
♪ All those fears
that made you cold ♪

39:34.664 --> 39:35.957
♪ I forgive them all ♪

39:36.041 --> 39:37.667
I'm scared I'm falling
in love with you.

39:37.751 --> 39:40.170
♪ Oh, the wind blows...

39:40.253 --> 39:42.005
I'm scared, too.

39:42.089 --> 39:44.382
♪ Far away
from this lonely town...

39:44.466 --> 39:46.760
We don't have
to fall in love, Ray.

39:48.762 --> 39:51.973
♪ In the darkest hour ♪

39:52.057 --> 39:54.184
♪ I'll spark a flame ♪

39:54.267 --> 39:55.936
♪ A heart that can't surrender ♪

39:56.019 --> 39:59.397
♪ Burns into a hostile blaze ♪

39:59.481 --> 40:02.317
♪ In the darkest hour ♪

40:02.400 --> 40:04.736
♪ You'll know my name ♪

40:04.820 --> 40:07.906
♪ I will hold the power...

40:07.989 --> 40:09.324
[Natalie] [over phone] What do
you mean the money

40:09.407 --> 40:11.493
just showed up? The bagman
told us it got stolen.

40:11.576 --> 40:13.870
I know, I'm kind
of freaking out.

40:13.954 --> 40:15.080
[Natalie chuckles]

40:15.163 --> 40:16.790
So, how does it feel to be rich?

40:16.873 --> 40:19.209
- Oh, you know...
- [glass shatters]

40:19.292 --> 40:20.752
[dog barking]

40:20.836 --> 40:22.295
[tires screeching in distance]

40:23.296 --> 40:24.840
I have to go.

40:29.594 --> 40:33.181
People tell all sorts of stories
about the game.

40:33.265 --> 40:35.225
But there are some things
they won't tell you.

40:35.308 --> 40:36.726
The fuck is that?

40:37.978 --> 40:40.438
[Ruby Anne] What do you think
it means?

40:44.985 --> 40:47.320
[Heather] No one knows
who invented Panic.

41:14.973 --> 41:17.225
And it turns out...

41:18.810 --> 41:20.103
- [shouts]
- [tires screeching]

41:20.187 --> 41:23.607
...no one knows
how to stop it, either.

41:25.192 --> 41:27.194
♪ ♪

41:57.224 --> 41:59.226
♪ ♪

42:29.256 --> 42:31.258
♪ ♪

43:01.288 --> 43:03.290
♪ ♪
